eu.ubitech.futuretpm.messages

Class ErrorMessages

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.ubitech.futuretpm.messages.ErrorMessages

  • public class ErrorMessages
extends java.lang.Object
    The ErrorMessages class is containing the various error messages of the app: This class includes 22 fields: {timeoutVolleyErrorMsg, noConnectionVolleyErrorMsg, serverVolleyErrorMsg, authFailureVolleyErrorMsg, parseVolleyErrorMsg, networkVolleyErrorMsg, unknownErrorMsg, unknownErrorRegistrationMsg, abortErrorMsg, timeoutErrorMsg, securityErrorMsg, notAllowedErrorMsg, attestationNotPrivateErrorMsg,constraintErrorMsg, dataErrorMsg, encodingErrorMsg, notSupportedErrorMsg, invalidStateErrorMsg, unKnownErrorMsg, nfcUnsupportedDeviceErrorMsg, inputErrorMsg, lastTransactionErrorMsg}

    a constructor ErrorMessages()

    a setter and a getter method for each field {getNoConnectionVolleyErrorMsg(), setNoConnectionVolleyErrorMsg(String), getTimeoutVolleyErrorMsg(), setTimeoutVolleyErrorMsg(String), getServerVolleyErrorMsg(), setServerVolleyErrorMsg(String), getAuthFailureVolleyErrorMsg(), setAuthFailureVolleyErrorMsg(String) getParseVolleyErrorMsg(), setParseVolleyErrorMsg(String), getNetworkVolleyErrorMsg(), setNetworkVolleyErrorMsg(String), getNotAllowedErrorMsg(), setNotAllowedErrorMsg(String), getUnknownErrorRegistrationMsg(), setUnknownErrorRegistrationMsg(String), getUnknownErrorMsg(), setUnknownErrorMsg(String), getAbortErrorMsg(), setAbortErrorMsg(String), getTimeoutErrorMsg(), setTimeoutErrorMsg(String), getSecurityErrorMsg(), setSecurityErrorMsg(String), getAttestationNotPrivateErrorMsg(), setAttestationNotPrivateErrorMsg(String), getDataErrorMsg(), setDataErrorMsg(String), getConstraintErrorMsg(), setConstraintErrorMsg(String), getEncodingErrorMsg(), setEncodingErrorMsg(String), {@link #setNotSupportedErrorMsg(String)}, , getInvalidStateErrorMsg(), setInvalidStateErrorMsg(String), getUnKnownErrorMsg(), setUnKnownErrorMsg(String), getInputErrorMsg(), setInputErrorMsg(String), getNfcUnsupportedDeviceErrorMsg(), setNfcUnsupportedDeviceErrorMsg(String)}
